Police have found a lorry transporting Sh3.5 million sugar that was abandoned on Saturday in Kamirithu, Limuru, following a robbery attempt. The lorry was transporting 29 tonnes of sugar to Nairobi from Transmara.Kiambu police boss Adiel Nyange said the seals of the trailer doors were tampered with but the thieves could not open them.The driver reported that he was hijacked.